ISLAMABAD, Dec 24 (APP):Minister of State for Information and Broadcasting Farrukh Habib said on Friday that FIA has submitted  challan in corruption case worth Rs 16 billion in anonymous accounts in the name of employees of Ramzan Sugar Mills.
In a tweet, he said after submission of  the challan by the FIA, PML- N Shahbaz Sharif has started hiding behind  adjournments.   Farrukh said that Shahbaz Sharif should not seek adjournments through his  lawyers but should call for trial on daily basis.
